article.headline: Akron 69, W Michigan 36
article.story: AKRON, Ohio (AP) -- Romeo Travis scored a game-high 17 points and Akron held Western Michigan to a single point in the first 12 1/2 minutes as the Zips won 69-36 on Saturday. Nick Dials added 12 points for Akron (15-4, 6-1 Mid-American Conference). Western Michigan (9-11 and 4-3) was led by Shawntes Gary with 8 points. Akron went ahead 12-1 with 13:41 to play in the first half on Quade Milum's two free throws before Western Michigan made its first basket, a layup by Gary with 12:39 left in the half. Akron led 24-13 at halftime, with Western Michigan shooting 18 percent in the first half. Milum widened Akron's lead to 40-21 with a layup with 14:34 to play. Western Michigan, trailing 54-34, managed one basket in the final seven minutes, a Derek Fracalossi layup with 4:41 to play.
